Is it just my bad luck since I mainly play mornings and days that I seem to think there are way too many patches that do absolutely no good at all.Last week,there was a 6 hr patch that turned into 8,for what? To revamp Kerra? I was there,and the very first night it was still bugged,you could not open any doors to ANY huts/ buildings...And the quests? I did a few,IMHO I didn't find any of the items useful.<br>
Then the next day,theres another 3 hr patch,for what? To fix the bugs from the first patch?<br>
Now today,theres yet another patch...I'm not even sure what today's is for.but I logged on at 9:56 am EST to a guildmate asking me, &quot;are you logging on to just log off?&quot;<br>
I was confused til she told me servers were coming down AGAIN....is it just me? I mean by the time the servers finally come back up,they will be crowded again,and everything camped...<br>
I guess it wouldn't be so bad if we knew about them ahead of time...a friend mentioned todays patch was posted on Friday at everquest.com,under scheduled maintenance....well,why should we have to go elsewhere to see when/ IF servers are coming down...they are so advanced,yet they can't put a message board up at the log in screen.If I have time to play EQ,I don't waste my time looking at other sites to see when servers will come down next...<br>
I'm sure I'll get a few flames,so be it,but isn't our time a little more valuable to verant? Silly me i forgot they just want our money...<br>
